==Text Compression==

Dialog text in Dragon Warrior IV uses a form of DTE (Dual Tile Encoding) compression where common character pairs are encoded as single bytes in the $90-$EF range.

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Range !! Description
|-
| $00-$8F || Direct character mapping (see table above)
|-
| $90-$EF || DTE pairs (two characters per byte)
|-
| $F0-$FF || Control codes
|}

